---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Documentation" includeHeader={true}>
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto py-12">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gradient mb-6">Documentation</h1>

    <div class="card space-y-6">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-cyan-300 mb-3">Getting Started</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4">
          Welcome to Easy Flags! This guide will help you set up feature flags
          in your application.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-300 mb-3">Creating a Space</h3>
        <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4">
          A space is your primary organizational unit. All feature flags and
          environments belong to a space.
        </p>
        <ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-slate-400 space-y-2 ml-4">
          <li>Navigate to Spaces</li>
          <li>Click "Create Space"</li>
          <li>Enter your space name and description</li>
          <li>Invite team members</li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-300 mb-3">Creating Features</h3>
        <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4">
          Features are the core of feature flag management. Create features to
          control rollouts.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-300 mb-3">Environments</h3>
        <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4">
          Environments allow you to have different feature flag values for
          different stages of your application.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
